text: Emma Terebo (born 10 July 1998) is a swimmer who represents New Caledonia.. At the 2015 Pacific Games, Terebo won eight gold medals, five in individual events and three in relays, including setting three games records in the individual events. In 2019, she competed at the 2019 Pacific Games held in Samoa. ==See also== * Swimming at the 2015 Pacific Games ==References== Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:New Caledonian female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics
